init_text: Humans once wielded formidable magical power. But with over 7 billion of us on the planet now, Mana has spread far too thinly to have any effect. When hostile aliens reduce humanity to a mere fraction, the survivors discover an old power has begun to reawaken once again.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Unbeknownst to Max, he had hit a level that caused mana to flow through his body, temporarily bestowing him with superhuman abilities.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She made a call, her first successful one in months, and talked to a friend about how Max could now get cell service.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "So he's a wizard or something?" asked Max's mother.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Some used it to pay bills, some to teleport between houses, and a few were even using the power of Mana to fly.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: the aliens were real until they destroyed the city of New York, and it was all captured on cell phones.
